  i SvelteMap is already reactive, wrapping it in $state() is unnecessary.
  
    6 │ 	// All built-in reactive classes wrapped unnecessarily.
  > 7 │ 	const map = $state(new SvelteMap());
      │ 	            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    8 │ 	const set = $state(new SvelteSet());
    9 │ 	const date = $state(new SvelteDate());
  
  i Classes from svelte/reactivity track their own mutations without needing a $state wrapper.
  
  i This rule belongs to the nursery group, which means it is not yet stable and may change in the future. Visit https://biomejs.dev/linter/#nursery for more information.
  
  i Unsafe fix: Remove the unnecessary $state() wrapper.
  
    6 │ → const·map·=·$state(new·SvelteMap());
      │               -------              -  

